  "prompt": "What causes fluttering eyes?",
  "response": "There are several potential causes of eye fluttering (eye twitching):\n\n1. Common, benign causes:\n- Stress\n- Fatigue\n- Caffeine consumption\n- Lack of sleep\n- Eye strain\n- Alcohol consumption\n- Dry eyes\n- Nutritional imbalances (low magnesium)\n\n2. Medical conditions:\n- Blepharospasm (involuntary eye muscle contractions)\n- Bell's palsy\n- Multiple sclerosis\n- Parkinson's disease\n- Brain or nerve disorders\n\n3. Other potential factors:\n- Allergies\n- Medication side effects\n- Excessive screen time\n- Bright lights\n- Wind or air irritation\n\nIn most cases, eye twitching is temporary and harmless. However, if twitching:\n- Persists for several weeks\n- Affects other parts of your face\n- Causes complete eye closure\n- Is accompanied by other symptoms\n\nYou should consult a healthcare professional to rule out more serious conditions.\n\nTreatment often involves:\n- Reducing stress\n- Getting adequate sleep\n- Limiting caffeine\n- Using eye drops\n- Taking breaks from screens\n- Managing underlying health issues",
